3. Find Equilibrium Index of a String
Problem Statement
You are given a string S consisting of lowercase English letters.
Each character has a weight equal to its position in the English alphabet
(a = 1, b = 2, ..., z = 26).
Find the smallest index (0-based) such that the sum of character weights to the left of that
index is equal to the sum of character weights to the right of that index.
The character at the equilibrium index should not be included in either sum.
If no such index exists, return -1.

Input Format
 A single string S

Output Format
 Print an integer representing the equilibrium index, or -1 if none exists.

Single character
Input: &quot;a&quot;
Output: 0
Balanced case
Input: &quot;bac&quot;
Weights: 2 | 1 | 3
Output: 1
No equilibrium
Input: &quot;abcd&quot;
Output: -1

// Java Code

import java.util.*;
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in);
        String s  = sc.next();
        int totalSum = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++) {
            totalSum += (s.charAt(i) - 'a' + 1); 
        }
        int leftSum = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++) {
            int currentweight = s.charAt(i) - 'a' + 1;
            int rightSum = totalSum - leftSum - currentweight;
            if(leftSum == rightSum) {
                System.out.println(i);
                return;
            }
            leftSum += currentweight;
        }
        System.out.println(-1);
    }
}
